# Development Workflow

## Core Flow

```
/spec-creation → /test-design + /code-design (parallel)
  → /api-contract (fullstack only) → /code-task
  → /code-execute (TDD: RED-GREEN-REFACTOR-REVIEW)
  → /exception-handler (backend/fullstack auto)
  → /code-test (integration/E2E/performance)
  → /spec-archive → /knowledge-continuum
```

## Entry Point

Use `/workflow-control "requirement"` as the single entry. It auto-detects mode (frontend/backend/fullstack), dispatches parallel branches, enforces HARD-GATEs, and supports interrupt recovery.

## Principles

- **Spec-First**: All development begins with /spec-creation (BDD format WITH WHEN-THEN)
- **Design-Driven**: /code-design produces architecture blueprints before any code
- **Test-Complete**: Unit tests in /code-execute, high-level tests in /code-test
- **Archive**: /spec-archive merges validated specs into enterprise spec library

## Mode Detection

- `frontend`: UI only, no database, no API contracts
- `backend`: Logic + data, skip frontend steps
- `fullstack`: All steps including api-contract

## HARD-GATE Checkpoints

- Step 5 (code-execute): test environment must be available before starting
- Step 5.5 (exception-handler): project convention scan must complete
- Step 6 (code-test): all unit tests from code-execute must pass
